1
00:02:45,320 --> 00:02:46,880
Lisa is dead.

2
00:02:47,880 --> 00:02:49,960
Then did she kill Cheng Hui?

3
00:02:53,360 --> 00:02:54,280
The preliminary autopsy shows

4
00:02:54,760 --> 00:02:56,000
Lisa's time of death

5
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,200
was before Cheng Hui's.

6
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:01,200
Lisa's child...

7
00:03:04,440 --> 00:03:06,720
No news might be good news.

8
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:09,680
Could it be that the child is already...

9
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:11,680
The child must be okay.

10
00:03:13,880 --> 00:03:14,600
I... Right.

11
00:03:15,160 --> 00:03:17,440
Where on earth would Cheng Hui hide the child?

12
00:03:19,160 --> 00:03:20,600
The child has been away from home for so long.

13
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:23,400
They'll need food and supplies.

14
00:03:26,240 --> 00:03:27,200
We can start by looking into children's products,

15
00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:28,320
that's one angle.

16
00:03:29,920 --> 00:03:30,680
Listen up.

17
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:32,760
We must find that child as soon as possible.

18
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:33,920
Yes, sir.

19
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:38,440
I haven't seen him.

20
00:03:41,080 --> 00:03:41,680
Thank you.

21
00:03:45,640 --> 00:03:46,680
How many stores has it been?

22
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:48,200
Thirteen. What's wrong?

23
00:03:49,040 --> 00:03:50,480
Can we get something to eat first?

24
00:03:53,160 --> 00:03:54,560
No, there's no time.

25
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:56,720
Can I just have one?

26
00:03:57,040 --> 00:03:58,400
Buying a loaf of bread should be fine, right?

27
00:03:59,080 --> 00:04:00,240
Please take a closer look.

28
00:04:03,480 --> 00:04:04,280
I haven't seen him.

29
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:09,840
Thanks, boss.

30
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:10,520
No problem.

31
00:04:10,920 --> 00:04:12,200
Any leads on your end?

32
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:22,040
Let's go.

33
00:04:22,040 --> 00:04:22,920
Thanks, boss.

34
00:04:23,120 --> 00:04:23,680
No problem.

35
00:04:25,840 --> 00:04:26,800
Let's go to the next one.

36
00:04:38,520 --> 00:04:39,280
Thanks.

37
00:04:46,480 --> 00:04:47,600
Why aren't you eating?

38
00:04:49,320 --> 00:04:50,200
I only brought one.

39
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:00,720
Share and share alike.

40
00:05:08,040 --> 00:05:08,800
Let's go.

41
00:05:19,960 --> 00:05:21,520
You guys, take a look at these.

42
00:05:26,720 --> 00:05:28,600
Is there a problem with this bill?

43
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:30,160
Didn't you notice she bought a lot?

44
00:05:30,160 --> 00:05:31,320
What's the problem with buying a lot?

45
00:05:31,520 --> 00:05:32,760
The point isn't the quantity.

46
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:34,680
The point is that in one go,

47
00:05:34,680 --> 00:05:36,760
she bought so much formula and baby food,

48
00:05:36,760 --> 00:05:38,320
and clothes for different stages of growth.

49
00:05:38,480 --> 00:05:39,760
That's right.

50
00:05:39,760 --> 00:05:41,360
This lady knows what she's talking about.

51
00:05:41,360 --> 00:05:42,480
Do you have children?

52
00:05:45,280 --> 00:05:47,880
When I was little, I often complained to my sister

53
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:50,880
about always having to wear her hand-me-downs.

54
00:05:53,600 --> 00:05:56,080
Formula and baby food don't keep for long.

55
00:05:56,200 --> 00:05:57,800
Besides, a child's height

56
00:05:57,800 --> 00:05:58,640
doesn't grow according to

57
00:05:58,640 --> 00:06:00,280
the different seasons.

58
00:06:00,280 --> 00:06:01,120
Most parents

59
00:06:01,120 --> 00:06:02,640
wouldn't buy so much at once.

60
00:06:08,400 --> 00:06:10,400
Why was there no change given for this bill?

61
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:14,000
That customer was very generous.

62
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:15,640
She even told us to hurry up and prepare the goods.

63
00:06:15,640 --> 00:06:16,920
And she paid an extra tip.

64
00:06:17,560 --> 00:06:19,120
But she never came to pick them up.

65
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:20,760
We couldn't reach her by phone either.

66
00:06:22,520 --> 00:06:23,720
We've compared the photos.

67
00:06:23,720 --> 00:06:24,560
It looks a lot like Lisa.

68
00:06:25,400 --> 00:06:26,560
What about the items? Are they still here?

69
00:06:26,560 --> 00:06:27,560
The items...

70
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:29,600
They were picked up by a courier a few days ago.

71
00:06:31,120 --> 00:06:32,400
Lisa is already...

72
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:34,920
Then who would have picked up those things?

73
00:06:36,080 --> 00:06:37,240
Do you have the delivery slip?

74
00:06:37,880 --> 00:06:38,800
The slip...

75
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:42,640
Now I remember.

76
00:06:42,640 --> 00:06:44,240
The courier was in a big hurry that day.

77
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:45,600
He didn't leave a slip with me.

78
00:06:46,760 --> 00:06:47,600
Do you remember

79
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:48,880
which courier company it was?

80
00:06:49,160 --> 00:06:51,600
I think there was a

81
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:52,800
coconut logo on the uniform.

82
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:58,480
Lisa bought so many things for her child.

83
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:00,360
The child must have been moved

84
00:07:00,360 --> 00:07:01,440
to a safe place.

85
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:04,320
Maybe Lisa

86
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:06,360
realized long ago

87
00:07:06,680 --> 00:07:07,880
what she would be facing.

88
00:07:11,080 --> 00:07:12,360
Let's hope she really did move the child

89
00:07:12,360 --> 00:07:13,840
to a safe place.

90
00:07:16,480 --> 00:07:18,000
Let's investigate the courier companies first.

91
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:19,360
If we find the delivery address,

92
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:21,400
we might be able to find her child.

93
00:07:24,280 --> 00:07:24,960
Let's go.

94
00:07:26,920 --> 00:07:27,560
Thank you.

95
00:07:37,840 --> 00:07:39,680
The one with a coconut pattern on the uniform

96
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:41,320
is Coconut King Express.

97
00:07:41,760 --> 00:07:42,400
Found it.

98
00:07:45,440 --> 00:07:46,160
Look.

99
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:47,840
The photo of that courier.

100
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:49,480
Impressive.

101
00:07:49,480 --> 00:07:50,600
Give it to me. I'll go check.

102
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:53,480
Do you have to go personally for such a small matter?

103
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:56,760
Young people need to use their brains when working.

104
00:07:57,320 --> 00:07:58,160
Leave it to me.

105
00:07:59,560 --> 00:08:00,840
That's rare.

106
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:03,160
Even Mei Dong is fighting for work.

107
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:08,480
How did it go?

108
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:10,120
This courier

109
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:12,400
resigned two days ago.

110
00:08:15,360 --> 00:08:16,800
Is it really that coincidental?

111
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:19,280
Get all the waybills

112
00:08:19,280 --> 00:08:20,880
of his recent deliveries

113
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:22,000
and check them one by one.

114
00:08:22,160 --> 00:08:22,760
Yes, sir.

115
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:24,800
Aren't you going?

116
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:32,200
Pa Xin.

117
00:08:34,160 --> 00:08:35,480
Are the autopsy results out?

118
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:42,960
The deceased has been dead for more than five days.

119
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:44,040
Cheng Hui

120
00:08:44,040 --> 00:08:45,520
couldn't have been killed by Lisa.

121
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:52,920
This is frostbite.

122
00:08:53,680 --> 00:08:54,040
Right.

123
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:56,360
But the true cause of death was

124
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:58,240
due to external pressure

125
00:08:58,240 --> 00:08:59,400
causing respiratory obstruction

126
00:08:59,560 --> 00:09:01,040
combined with foreign objects blocking the airway,

127
00:09:01,360 --> 00:09:02,360
resulting in asphyxiation.

128
00:09:04,680 --> 00:09:05,760
Lisa was buried inside

129
00:09:05,760 --> 00:09:07,640
the elephant sculpture, causing suffocation.

130
00:09:07,960 --> 00:09:08,480
Correct.

131
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:15,600
Burying Lisa alive inside the elephant sculpture...

132
00:09:15,920 --> 00:09:17,120
this corresponds to the Earth element.

133
00:09:18,480 --> 00:09:20,920
To complete the secret art using Metal, Wood, Water, Fire, Earth.

134
00:09:21,880 --> 00:09:23,160
So the Secret Art of Wealth

135
00:09:23,160 --> 00:09:24,520
that Na Aluo mentioned is this.

136
00:09:24,520 --> 00:09:25,680
Metal, Wood, Water, Fire, Earth.

137
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:27,080
What does that mean?

138
00:09:27,360 --> 00:09:29,240
The five punishments of Metal, Wood, Water, Fire, Earth

139
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:30,440
correspond respectively to

140
00:09:30,440 --> 00:09:32,800
pouring molten metal into the ears,

141
00:09:33,040 --> 00:09:34,360
confinement in a wooden box,

142
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:36,040
immersion in ice blocks,

143
00:09:36,040 --> 00:09:38,320
roasting the body with fire, and live burial.

144
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:40,280
Legend has it that completing this secret art

145
00:09:40,560 --> 00:09:42,640
grants the practitioner wealth.

146
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:48,240
Cheng Hui killed Lisa's parents,

147
00:09:48,440 --> 00:09:50,120
and tortured Lisa to death.

148
00:09:50,560 --> 00:09:51,880
He even wanted to use Lisa

149
00:09:51,880 --> 00:09:53,480
to perform some Secret Art of Wealth.

150
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:56,160
What a jerk.

151
00:09:57,320 --> 00:09:58,160
Jerk.

152
00:10:01,840 --> 00:10:03,160
Not yet, huh?

153
00:10:04,560 --> 00:10:05,320
Okay.

154
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:12,320
My throat is parched.

155
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:16,040
I haven't found anything here.

156
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,200
How about over there?

157
00:10:18,760 --> 00:10:19,920
Come take a look at this.

158
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:29,680
This tracking number

159
00:10:29,960 --> 00:10:31,320
matches the tracking number

160
00:10:31,320 --> 00:10:33,200
the courier used to pick up goods at the mother and baby store.

161
00:10:33,520 --> 00:10:34,760
The volume size also matches.

162
00:10:34,920 --> 00:10:36,280
Have you contacted the recipient?

163
00:10:37,960 --> 00:10:38,600
Hello.

164
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:40,720
The number you dialed does not exist.

165
00:10:40,720 --> 00:10:41,480
It's a non-existent number.

166
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:45,200
Hanling, North 9th Lane, No. 85.

167
00:10:45,400 --> 00:10:46,760
This place is very popular right now.

168
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:50,320
There's a tree over in Hanling.

169
00:10:50,320 --> 00:10:51,560
They say it's a Divine Tree.

170
00:10:52,120 --> 00:10:53,160
I don't know how it got so popular.

171
00:10:53,160 --> 00:10:54,440
And wishes made there are very effective.

172
00:10:54,640 --> 00:10:55,640
Many people have already

173
00:10:55,640 --> 00:10:57,440
started businesses making wishes on behalf of others.

174
00:10:57,440 --> 00:10:58,920
And the commission is quite high.

175
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:00,840
For real?

176
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:03,080
You're making me want to go pray there too.

177
00:11:03,920 --> 00:11:04,720
Perfect.

178
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:05,720
Let's go.

179
00:11:06,680 --> 00:11:07,240
Wait, no.

180
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:09,640
It's not that I don't want to go.

181
00:11:09,640 --> 00:11:11,200
It's a four-hour drive to get there.

182
00:11:11,360 --> 00:11:13,200
And the mountain road is really bumpy.

183
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:14,600
I... I don't think it's necessary.

184
00:11:14,600 --> 00:11:15,760
You can make a couple of wishes when you get there.

185
00:11:15,760 --> 00:11:17,040
It's really all winding mountain roads.

186
00:11:17,040 --> 00:11:17,800
We're driving. Let's go.

187
00:11:44,800 --> 00:11:46,440
The navigation says this is the place.

188
00:11:48,960 --> 00:11:50,240
Aren't there any other roads?

189
00:11:51,640 --> 00:11:52,920
Looks like we have to go into the mountains.

190
00:11:53,280 --> 00:11:55,280
We'll have to go the rest of the way on foot.

191
00:11:56,120 --> 00:11:57,840
Making a wish in a dump like this...

192
00:11:58,520 --> 00:11:59,720
could it possibly come true?

193
00:12:00,920 --> 00:12:03,280
Spend ten or twenty yuan on some colorful ropes,

194
00:12:03,280 --> 00:12:04,560
hang them on the Divine Tree,

195
00:12:04,640 --> 00:12:06,040
and you dare to wish for anything.

196
00:12:07,640 --> 00:12:08,640
Do you think it works?

197
00:12:10,240 --> 00:12:11,120
Asking someone for a favor...

198
00:12:11,120 --> 00:12:12,680
costs more than ten or twenty yuan.

199
00:12:16,520 --> 00:12:17,160
Let's go.

200
00:12:34,160 --> 00:12:35,160
You guys go ahead.

201
00:12:35,160 --> 00:12:35,840
Let's go.

202
00:13:15,120 --> 00:13:16,280
This is the right place, isn't it?

203
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:33,880
Number 84 is here.

204
00:13:35,040 --> 00:13:36,120
From the looks of it,

205
00:13:36,280 --> 00:13:38,360
it doesn't seem like a place where people live.

206
00:13:41,720 --> 00:13:42,720
Let's take a look first.

207
00:13:56,480 --> 00:13:58,000
I heard this village...

208
00:13:58,320 --> 00:13:59,560
used to be quite prosperous.

209
00:14:00,040 --> 00:14:01,240
Most of Tuo City's grain...

210
00:14:01,240 --> 00:14:02,240
came from here.

211
00:14:02,800 --> 00:14:04,440
I don't know when it started,

212
00:14:04,880 --> 00:14:06,280
but this place ended up like this.

213
00:14:09,120 --> 00:14:09,880
Let's go over there.

214
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:31,440
This is Number 86.

215
00:14:32,160 --> 00:14:33,560
That was 84 just now.

216
00:14:33,760 --> 00:14:35,120
I don't see Number 85.

217
00:14:37,760 --> 00:14:39,200
Let's keep searching along the mountain path.

218
00:14:40,400 --> 00:14:41,040
Go.

219
00:14:56,800 --> 00:14:58,040
So this is the Divine Tree.

220
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:00,400
That's not hard to tell, is it?

221
00:15:30,800 --> 00:15:32,320
Number 85 is actually here.

222
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:35,360
It must be from the rain washing it away,

223
00:15:35,360 --> 00:15:36,640
causing a landslide.

224
00:15:37,040 --> 00:15:38,960
Number 85 must be buried under here.

225
00:15:40,560 --> 00:15:42,280
But if the house is buried,

226
00:15:42,640 --> 00:15:44,440
why would Lisa send her child here?

227
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:45,920
Maybe...

228
00:15:45,920 --> 00:15:47,560
she arranged to meet someone here.

229
00:15:49,160 --> 00:15:51,840
Meeting under this Divine Tree...

230
00:15:52,600 --> 00:15:54,000
is a bit too strange.

231
00:16:05,680 --> 00:16:06,360
Ma'am.

232
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:10,120
Why did you come here to make a wish?

233
00:16:11,960 --> 00:16:13,040
This tree...

234
00:16:13,040 --> 00:16:14,560
is the embodiment of a god.

235
00:16:14,960 --> 00:16:16,080
The embodiment of a god?

236
00:16:17,400 --> 00:16:18,280
A long time ago,

237
00:16:18,480 --> 00:16:20,080
there was a kind woman.

238
00:16:20,320 --> 00:16:21,720
Her husband abused her.

239
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:24,160
When she escaped to this tree,

240
00:16:24,760 --> 00:16:26,200
she was on the verge of death.

241
00:16:26,520 --> 00:16:28,080
She couldn't even walk anymore.

242
00:16:28,080 --> 00:16:29,960
So she came here to make a wish before she died?

243
00:16:31,960 --> 00:16:33,440
Not only did she not die,

244
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:35,080
but her abusive husband...

245
00:16:35,080 --> 00:16:37,360
died mysteriously overnight.

246
00:16:38,040 --> 00:16:39,520
When the news spread,

247
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:42,240
the number of people coming to this tree to make a wish...

248
00:16:42,240 --> 00:16:43,640
just grew and grew.

249
00:16:44,160 --> 00:16:45,320
The embodiment of a god...

250
00:16:45,760 --> 00:16:49,000
helps people punish the injustices of this world.

251
00:16:58,680 --> 00:17:00,280
Usually, worship and making wishes...

252
00:17:00,280 --> 00:17:01,680
are meant to guide people toward goodness.

253
00:17:01,680 --> 00:17:02,720
But this Divine Tree...

254
00:17:02,720 --> 00:17:03,840
seems to be guiding people...

255
00:17:03,840 --> 00:17:05,800
to make wishes for revenge...

256
00:17:05,800 --> 00:17:07,120
or curses.

257
00:17:07,920 --> 00:17:09,240
August 15th.

258
00:17:10,040 --> 00:17:11,520
An abused wife.

259
00:17:11,840 --> 00:17:13,480
Isn't this a bit too much of a coincidence?

260
00:17:13,760 --> 00:17:15,400
Could it be related to Cheng Hui's case?

261
00:17:17,320 --> 00:17:18,280
A case?

262
00:17:18,680 --> 00:17:20,280
What does it have to do with the Divine Tree?

263
00:17:20,280 --> 00:17:21,520
Can a tree kill people?

264
00:17:28,560 --> 00:17:29,560
There's someone over there.

265
00:18:01,520 --> 00:18:01,960
Director.

266
00:18:02,520 --> 00:18:03,840
Have you seen this child?

267
00:18:07,800 --> 00:18:09,120
That's A Dong.

268
00:18:12,720 --> 00:18:15,040
Then do you remember who brought him here?

269
00:18:15,320 --> 00:18:16,800
The children here...

270
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:18,760
are mostly brought in by the community...

271
00:18:18,960 --> 00:18:20,720
or police officers.

272
00:18:21,480 --> 00:18:23,280
But A Dong's situation...

273
00:18:23,760 --> 00:18:24,840
is a bit special.

274
00:18:26,280 --> 00:18:27,400
He was...

275
00:18:27,760 --> 00:18:29,960
abandoned at the entrance of the orphanage.

276
00:18:30,320 --> 00:18:31,280
Abandoned?

277
00:18:31,800 --> 00:18:32,640
At that time,

278
00:18:33,120 --> 00:18:34,480
he was asleep.

279
00:18:34,480 --> 00:18:35,520
Next to him,

280
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:39,080
there was a lot of food and clothing.

281
00:18:39,320 --> 00:18:40,880
Then can we go see him?

282
00:18:47,480 --> 00:18:48,240
Okay.
